<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,630,797]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName authority="Sreedevi &amp; Ranasinghe &amp; Fabrizi &amp; Ahrens, 2019" authorityName="Sreedevi &amp; Ranasinghe &amp; Fabrizi &amp; Ahrens" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,467,630,656]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viraktamathi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,467,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Maladera viraktamathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[479,574,630,656]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brenske, 1898)" authorityName="Brenske" authorityYear="1898" baseAuthorityName="Brenske" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[715,1071,630,656]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="servitrita">
<emphasis box="[715,866,631,656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M. servitrita</emphasis>
(Brenske, 1898)
</taxonomicName>
in its external and genital morphology. The new species differs from the latter by the anterior margin of the pronotum having a medially widely lacking marginal line as well as by the shape of the aedeagus; the left aedeagal process with insertion of left paramere is produced more distally, the left paramere bears a longitudinal dorsal sublateral carina, which is absent in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brenske" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[615,762,771,796]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="servitrita">
<emphasis box="[615,762,771,796]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M. servitrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,324,836,862]" box="[189,324,836,862]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,836,862]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,836,862]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1398,882,979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">This new species name (noun in the genitive case) is dedicated to the Indian leafhopper taxonomist and entomologist, Prof. Chandrasekhara A. Viraktamath, in recognition of his colossal work on leafhopper taxonomy.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
